<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00541</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REQUIRING HEALTHCARE FACILITIES TO PROVIDE A PRICE LIST OF ITS HEALTHCARE SERVICES INCLUDING INCIDENTAL EXPENSES AND MEDICAL SUPPLIES THAT CAN BE CHARGED IN THE MEDICAL BILL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Healthcare Services Price Disclosure Act Of 2016.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : States that learning the price in advance enables the public to make informed judgement of the cost they would spend upon admission of the patients.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>YAP, VICTOR A.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-06-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Reform</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Panotes (039 2016-10-19)</td><td>2. Espino (047 2016-11-22)</td><tr><td>3. Primicias-Agabas (060 2017-01-23)</td><td>4. Fortun (000 2018-09-20)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2016-07-27</td></tr></table>